Package edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_hire.model.manager

Class WolfHire

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_hire.model.manager.WolfHire
  • public class WolfHire
extends java.lang.Object
    Concrete class that maintains a list of Positions and their associated application lists, the active position, and handles commands from the GUI. WolfHire class implements the Singleton Design Pattern, where it constructs a single instance of itself to implement functionality. Singleton Design Pattern means that only one instance of, in this case WolfHire, can ever be created. It ensures that all parts of WolgHireGUI are interacting with the same WolfHire instance at all times.
    Author:
    hmreese2

    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static WolfHire getInstance()
        Implements Singleton design pattern. Creates the one single instance of WolfHire that is ever used. getInstance() checks if the singleton is null. If it is, getInstance() calls private WolfHire() constructor to create single instance.
        Returns:
        a single instance of WolfHire using the singleton design pattern

      • loadPositionsFromFile

        public void loadPositionsFromFile​(java.lang.String fileName)
        Loads Position information(s) from file and reads/processes contents using PositionReader. The returned list of Positions are added to the positions field. The first position in the list returned from PositionReader is made the activePosition. Works closely with PositionReader io class to correctly load in file and file contents.
        Parameters:
        fileName - name of file that is being loaded

      • savePositionsToFile

        public void savePositionsToFile​(java.lang.String fileName)
        Saves positions to a file. Works closely with PositionWriter io class to correctly write list of positions contents to file
        Parameters:
        fileName - name of file being written to
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with message "Unable to save file." if activePosition is null, or issue in saving file (thrown in PositionWriter).

      • addNewPosition

        public void addNewPosition​(java.lang.String positionName,
                           int hoursPerWeek,
                           int payRate)
        Creates a new position with the given info and adds it to the end of the WolfHire Positions list. Position is then loaded as the "activePosition" by calling the loadPosition(String positionName) method.
        Parameters:
        positionName - name of position
        hoursPerWeek - hours per week worked for a position
        payRate - rate of pay for a position
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with message "Position cannot be created." if positionName parameter is null, empty string, or duplicate of an existing position-name (CASE-SENSITIVE).

      • loadPosition

        public void loadPosition​(java.lang.String positionName)
        Finds Position with the given name in the list, makes it active or activePosition, and sets the application id for that position so that any new Applications added to position are created with the next correct id.
        Parameters:
        positionName - name of position being loaded
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with message "Position not available." if there is not position with the given name.

      • getActivePosition

      • deleteApplicationById

        public void deleteApplicationById​(int id)

        Parameters:
        id - id of application being deleted.

      • getApplicationsAsArray

        public java.lang.String[][] getApplicationsAsArray​(java.lang.String filter)
        Displays application list as 2D String array list. Format: a row for every application in activePosition, 4 columns (id, state, unityId, reviewer)
        Parameters:
        filter - string that represents what item the arrays need to be filtered by (either *State option, or All which lists all information).
        Returns:
        2D String array list of applications filtered by either their state, of filter value is *State, or by listing all information if filter value is "All" Or null if there is no activePosition

      • getApplicationById

        public Application getApplicationById​(int id)
        Locates an application from activePosition using given id and returns it
        Parameters:
        id - id of potential application in activePosition
        Returns:
        application that matches given id, or null if there is no application with the given id in the activePosition
